maxLinesSection titled “maxLines”
This option sets the maximum number of lines allowed in a function body.
If the function body exceeds this limit, a diagnostic will be reported.
Default:50
WhenmaxLines: 2, the following function will be considered invalid:
{  "linter": {    "rules": {      "complexity": {        "noExcessiveLinesPerFunction": {          "options": {            "maxLines":           }        }      }    }  }}
1function example() {2 const a = 1; // 13 const b = 2; // 24 const c = 3; // };
